Key Match Events: Phoenix Suns center Jusuf Nurkic made the game-winning free throw after an uncalled loose ball foul.
Luka Doncic missed an open three-pointer in the final two minutes that could have put the Mavericks up by five.
Others: Dallas Mavericks struggled with offensive rebounding, missing Dereck Lively II.
Jason Kidd's decision to play Spencer Dinwiddie in clutch minutes instead of Naji Marshall was questionable.
Dallas Mavericks' three-point shooting was poor, with a 11/33 performance from deep, bringing their season average to 35.2%.
